section.section:
If an action to foreclose the right of redemption has not been filed, and the property is redeemed more than 4 months after the date of the tax sale, the holder of a certificate of sale may be reimbursed for the following expenses actually incurred:
costs for recording the certificate of sale;
a title search fee, not to exceed $250;
the postage and certified mailing costs for the notices required under § 14-833(a-1) of this title; and
reasonable attorney's fees, not to exceed $500.
